article.headline: Texas Tech 83, Baylor 76
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas -- Alan Voskuil and John Roberson each scored 18 points to lead Texas Tech over Baylor 83-76 on Saturday night, ending the Red Raiders' four-game losing streak. Baylor let a 12-point lead midway through the second half evaporate and scored only one field goal in the final 3:29 of the game in its fifth straight loss. Back-to-back steals by Michael Prince and D'walyn Roberts with less than 2 minutes remaining kept the Bears from pulling close down the stretch. Curtis Jerrels scored 20 points and Kevin Rogers added 17 points for Baylor (15-8, 3-6 Big 12). Texas Tech (11-12, 2-6) outrebounded the Bears 38-27. Baylor missed only one free throw in 23 attempts but it wasn't enough.
